Build the Code

To build the code and deploy the Python environment, execute the following command: This command will execute the Ansible playbook orchestrate.yml, which automates the deployment process. You will be prompted to enter the password for sudo privileges.

make build


Run the Server
Once the code is built and deployed, you can run the FastAPI server using the following command: This command starts the FastAPI server, listening on host 0.0.0.0 and port 8000.

make server

Verify the Server
To verify that the server is running correctly, you can use curl to make a GET request to the /hello endpoint: This command sends a GET request to the server running on localhost at port 8000 and expects a response from the /hello endpoint.

make verify


